<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A more realistic valuation method =
here is not to worry about cash flows at all =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>as Trump SP=
AC clearly does not=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94 and treat the stock simply as a tok=
en of public interest in Donald Trump. My guess is that the price of Trump =
SPAC stock will not, for instance, be much affected by its earnings announc=
ements, unless Trump himself does the earnings calls in which case it will =
go up no matter what he says. My guess is that the stock will not be partic=
ularly correlated with the stocks of other media or technology companies. M=
y guess is that the stock will go up when Trump is on television, or if he =
announces that he=E2=80=99s running for president again. My guess is that i=
f something <em>bad </em>happens to Trump =E2=80=94 if he=E2=80=99s sued or=
 arrested or banned by a new tech company or some new scandal comes out =E2=
=80=94 then that will=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>make the stock go up, to own =
the libs or whatever. My guess is that each day that goes by without Trump =
news, the stock will go down a bit. My guess is that the stock is essential=
ly a bet on Trump=E2=80=99s personal newsiness, on Trump-news volatility.</=
p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, that was in 2021, and I think it turned=
