ss, yes, but also on its own connection with Trump=E2=80=99s newsiness. In =
2021, when this was announced, people were like =E2=80=9Cooh Trump SPAC=E2=
=80=9D and bought the stock, and for a while the stock did sort of correlat=
e with Trump=E2=80=99s newsiness. But after years of delays and not doing m=
uch, DWAC no longer seemed like a good way to bet on Trump=E2=80=99s newsin=
ess, and it just faded from public attention. Also the price dropped. DWAC =
hit $97.54 per share in March 2022; it was below $18 two weeks ago.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But, I dunno, here it is again. It closed at $=
